Process called "analyze_protocol_performance" that takes protocols as List[IoTProtocol] and analysis_config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns ProtocolAnalysisResult:
    Let latency_analysis be analyze_protocol_latency with protocols as protocols
    Let throughput_analysis be analyze_protocol_throughput with protocols as protocols
    Let reliability_analysis be analyze_protocol_reliability with protocols as protocols
    Let energy_analysis be analyze_protocol_energy_consumption with protocols as protocols
    Let security_analysis be analyze_protocol_security_performance with protocols as protocols
    Let comparative_analysis be compare_protocols_against_benchmarks with protocols as protocols and analyses as [latency_analysis, throughput_analysis, reliability_analysis, energy_analysis]
    Let optimization_recommendations be generate_optimization_recommendations with analyses as [latency_analysis, throughput_analysis, reliability_analysis, energy_analysis, security_analysis]
    Return ProtocolAnalysisResult with:
        analyzed_protocols as extract_protocol_ids with protocols as protocols
        latency_metrics as latency_analysis.metrics
        throughput_metrics as throughput_analysis.metrics
        reliability_metrics as reliability_analysis.metrics
        energy_metrics as energy_analysis.metrics
        security_metrics as security_analysis.metrics
        comparative_analysis as comparative_analysis
        optimization_recommendations as optimization_recommendations
        performance_score as calculate_overall_performance_score with analyses as [latency_analysis, throughput_analysis, reliability_analysis, energy_analysis, security_analysis]
        bottlenecks_identified as identify_performance_bottlenecks with analyses as [latency_analysis, throughput_analysis, reliability_analysis, energy_analysis]
        improvement_potential as calculate_improvement_potential with analyses as [latency_analysis, throughput_analysis, reliability_analysis, energy_analysis]
        analysis_timestamp as get_current_timestamp

